CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F381A1733953035
OL,3,CTerminally ill man waits two months
OL,4,Cfor social security support
OL,6,F"They're then watching me trying to
OL,7,Frun around and sort something out that
OL,8,FI shouldn't have to deal with.
OL,10,F"There should be somebody within the
OL,11,Fsystem that says, 'Right, that person
OL,12,Fis terminally ill; I will deal with
OL,13,Fthat.'
OL,15,F"When you're terminally ill, the
OL,16,Fclock's ticking."
OL,18,FWayne adds that whilst his prognosis
OL,19,Fis one or two years, many are given
OL,20,Fonly a few months to live at the point
OL,21,Fof receiving a terminal diagnosis.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/9
