OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F381A1733953035
OL,3,CTerminally ill man waits two months
OL,4,Cfor social security support
OL,6,FHe furthers: "I'm quite lucky because
OL,7,Fhopefully, I'll go one or two years,
OL,8,Fbut if I wasn't (...) imagine you're
OL,9,Fon your death's door, if you've got
OL,10,Ffour weeks to live, and you're having
OL,11,Fto spend that time battling with
OL,12,Fbureaucracy."
OL,14,FHis friends and family have helped him
OL,15,Fget by as he's spent time in between
OL,16,Fchemotherapy sessions completing
OL,17,Fsocial security forms, but Wayne says
OL,18,Fhe feels he's been failed by a system
OL,19,Fhe's spent his life contributing
OL,20,Ftowards.
